---
import { loadEnv } from "../env";
const env = loadEnv();
const tallyUrl = `https://tally.so/r/${env.TALLY_FORM_ID}`;
---
<section class="section hero" data-section-num="01" id="s01" aria-labelledby="hero-headline">
  <div class="hero-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">rntme · pilot program · 2026</div>
    <h1 id="hero-headline">Stop reinventing a backend every time your agent builds you one.</h1>
    <p class="lede hero-lede">
      Your first Cursor-built approval tool shipped in two days. The fourth one has a schema
      you've never seen, events that half-work, and a review queue nobody reads.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-pitch">
      rntme is a standard runtime for these services. One blueprint describes the domain,
      the data, the state, the API, and the UI. The runtime enforces it.
      Service&nbsp;#10 looks like service&nbsp;#1.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href={tallyUrl}>Apply as a pilot team →</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={env.GITHUB_URL} rel="noopener">
        See it on GitHub
        <svg class="btn-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M5.5 3h-2A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 2 4.5v6A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 3.5 12h6a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5-1.5v-2"/>
          <path d="M8 2h4v4"/><path d="m6.5 7.5 5-5"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div>Runtime<br/><b>event-sourced</b></div>
      <div>Unit of work<br/><b>validated JSON</b></div>
      <div>Output<br/><b>API + UI + events</b></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero-pitch { max-width: 62ch; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
</style>
